<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000046#     2#         1233#">Va. Code Ann. § 46.2-1233</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_46.2-1233"/><heading><desig>§ 46.2-1233.</desig><title>Localities may regulate towing fees</title></heading><bodyText><p>The governing body of any locality may by ordinance set reasonable limits on fees charged for the removal of motor vehicles, trailers, and parts thereof left on private property in violation of <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 46.2-1231"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 46.2-1231">§ 46.2-1231<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000046#     2#         1231#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, and for the removal of trespassing vehicles under <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 46.2-1215"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 46.2-1215">§ 46.2-1215<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000046#     2#         1215#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, taking into consideration the fair market value of such removal.</p><p>Localities in Planning District 8 shall establish by ordinance (i) a hookup and initial towing fee of $ 135 and (ii) for towing a vehicle between seven o'clock p.m. and eight o'clock a.m. or on any Saturday, Sunday, or holiday, an additional fee of $ 25 per instance; however, such ordinance shall also provide that in no event shall more than two such additional fees be charged for towing any vehicle.</p></bodyText><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p>Code 1950, § 46-541; 1952, c. 352; 1954, c. 435; 1958, c. 541, § 46.1-551; 1978, cc. 202, 335; 1979, c. 132; 1983, c. 34; 1985, c. 375; <citation normalizedCite="1989 VA CH 17"><content><span normalizedCite="1989 Va. Ch. 17">1989, cc. 17<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1989#000017#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation normalizedCite="1989 VA CH 727"><content><span normalizedCite="1989 Va. Ch. 727">727<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1989#000727#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="1990 VA CH 502"><content><span normalizedCite="1990 Va. Ch. 502">1990, cc. 502<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1990#000502#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation normalizedCite="1990 VA CH 571"><content><span normalizedCite="1990 Va. Ch. 571">571<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1990#000571#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation normalizedCite="1990 VA CH 573"><content><span normalizedCite="1990 Va. Ch. 573">573<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1990#000573#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="2016 VA CH 476"><content><span normalizedCite="2016 Va. Ch. 476">2016, c. 476<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2016#000476#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></historyItem></historyGroup></history></level></statute></legislativeDocBody><metadata><dc:metadata xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><dc:identifier identifierScheme="PGUID">urn:contentItem:5K